**Segments**

- **Type:** N-butanol is available in two forms - bio-based n-butanol and synthetic n-butanol. Bio-based n-butanol is derived from renewable sources like biomass, whereas synthetic n-butanol is produced from petrochemicals.

- **Application:** N-butanol finds applications across various industries such as chemicals, pharmaceuticals, paints & coatings, adhesives, and others. In the chemicals industry, it is used as a solvent and intermediate in the production of various chemicals. In the pharmaceutical industry, it is utilized in the manufacturing of medicines. Furthermore, in paints & coatings, n-butanol serves as a solvent that enhances the application properties of coatings.

- **End-Use:** The end-use segments of the n-butanol market include automotive, construction, healthcare, and others. In the automotive sector, n-butanol is used in the manufacturing of automotive coatings and adhesives. In the construction industry, it is employed in paints, coatings, and sealants. Moreover, in healthcare, n-butanol is used in the production of medicines and medical devices.

