In terms of applications, n-butanol serves a crucial role as a solvent and intermediate in the production of chemicals in the chemicals industry. The pharmaceutical sector relies on n-butanol for the manufacturing of medicines, highlighting its importance in the healthcare field. Additionally, the paints & coatings industry benefits from n-butanol as a solvent that improves coating application properties, contributing to the durability and aesthetics of various products.

The end-use segments of the n-butanol market further illustrate the versatility of this chemical compound. In the automotive industry, n-butanol is utilized in the formulation of automotive coatings and adhesives, essential for enhancing the performance and appearance of vehicles. The construction sector leverages n-butanol in paints, coatings, and sealants, emphasizing its role in protecting and beautifying architectural structures. Furthermore, in the healthcare domain, n-butanol plays a vital role in the production of medicines and medical devices, ensuring quality and efficiency in healthcare products.

